{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017FxsZkNhJRULakRiDibY3Q","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /tmp/fdb-12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow-20260517T195737Z/dev/plans/runs/12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow-output.json has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0166efe2-5172-4c6f-950f-26b3875cd45a","uuid":"c01cc658-00b4-4b58-91ac-3044d0cedb66","timestamp":"2026-05-17T19:58:32.663Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow-20260517T195737Z/dev/plans/runs/12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow-output.json","oldString":"  \"head_sha\": \"f2f21b59338a706de625096b099b041e01c1a1c2\",\n  \"commits\": [],","newString":"  \"head_sha\": \"05b08af\",\n  \"commits\": [\"05b08af: docs(12-B): blocker report — benchmark-and-robustness substrate absent\"],","originalFile":"{\n  \"phase\": \"12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow\",\n  \"baseline_sha\": \"f2f21b59338a706de625096b099b041e01c1a1c2\",\n  \"branch\": \"phase-12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow-20260517T195737Z\",\n  \"head_sha\": \"f2f21b59338a706de625096b099b041e01c1a1c2\",\n  \"commits\": [],\n  \"workflow_file\": \".github/workflows/benchmark-and-robustness.yml\",\n  \"workflow_line_count\": 0,\n  \"jobs_restored\": [],\n  \"jobs_dropped\": [\n    \"go-fuzz-smoke (no go/ surface in 0.6.0 — definitive per ci-deferred.md)\"\n  ],\n  \"scripts_restored_or_added\": [],\n  \"dry_run_supported\": false,\n  \"actionlint_result\": \"n/a — no workflow written\",\n  \"agent_verify_result\": \"not run — STOPPED at blocker surfacing per prompt instruction\",\n  \"blockers_encountered\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B1\",\n      \"item\": \"rust-benchmarks\",\n      \"missing\": \"scripts/run-benchmarks.sh + cargo bench target\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"scripts_run_benchmarks_sh\": \"absent in current tree (ls scripts/ shows no run-benchmarks.sh)\",\n        \"fathomdb_benches\": \"absent (src/rust/crates/fathomdb has no benches/ dir; Cargo.toml is pure facade, no [[bench]] entry, no criterion dep)\",\n        \"pre_0_6_0_script\": \"git show 39ee271^:scripts/run-benchmarks.sh ran `cargo bench -p fathomdb --bench production_paths --features sqlite-vec` — neither bench nor feature exists in 0.6.0 facade crate\"\n      },\n      \"option_a_viable\": false,\n      \"rationale_a_rejected\": \"Pre-0.6.0 substrate ran against a wholly different Rust crate shape (single `fathomdb` crate with criterion benches + sqlite-vec feature). 0.6.0 facade crate is a re-export shell; resurrecting `production_paths` bench is net-new authorship of a benchmark harness against a redesigned engine, not restoration. Violates `feedback_reliability_principles` net-negative-LoC bias and `delete-before-add` discipline — that's a Pack 7 perf-evidence slice, explicitly out-of-scope per prompt header.\",\n      \"option_b_recommendation\": \"Omit rust-benchmarks job entirely from initial workflow landing. Track restoration in ci-deferred.md as Pack 7 dependency.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B2\",\n      \"item\": \"rust-scale-tests\",\n      \"missing\": \"fathomdb-engine `scale` integration test target\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"engine_tests_dir\": \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/ — listed contents have no scale.rs (closest matches: durability_soak.rs, perf_gates.rs, neither is a `scale` test)\",\n        \"pre_0_6_0_invocation\": \"cargo nextest run -p fathomdb --test scale (pre-0.6.0 crate name; renamed to fathomdb-engine in 0.6.0)\"\n      },\n      \"option_a_viable\": false,\n      \"rationale_a_rejected\": \"No scale.rs ever existed in the 0.6.0-rewrite engine substrate; authoring one is Pack 7 territory.\",\n      \"option_b_recommendation\": \"Omit rust-scale-tests; or substitute `durability_soak` if orchestrator wants the slot occupied — though `durability_soak` violates `feedback_reliability_principles` (no soak). Recommend: drop.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B3\",\n      \"item\": \"rust-tracing-stress\",\n      \"missing\": \"fathomdb-engine `tracing` cargo feature AND `tracing_events` test\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"engine_cargo_toml_features\": \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml has no [features] section at all — `--features tracing` will fail with `Package fathomdb-engine v0.6.0 does not have feature 'tracing'`\",\n        \"tracing_events_test\": \"absent (closest: trace_source_ref.rs which is unrelated)\",\n        \"tracing_events_continue_under_concurrent_load\": \"function does not exist\"\n      },\n      \"option_a_viable\": false,\n      \"rationale_a_rejected\": \"Requires adding a cargo feature + writing a tracing-stress test against current engine — net-new production-surface work, not workflow restoration.\",\n      \"option_b_recommendation\": \"Drop rust-tracing-stress job. Defer to whenever tracing-events instrumentation lands as a Phase 12+ slice.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B4\",\n      \"item\": \"python-stress-tests\",\n      \"missing\": \"src/python/tests/test_stress.py\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"tests_dir_listing\": \"src/python/tests/: conftest.py, test_errors.py, test_ffi_safety.py, test_no_recovery_surface.py, test_property_template.py, test_save_time_validation.py, test_scaffold.py, test_surface.py, test_typed_errors.py — no test_stress.py\"\n      },\n      \"option_a_viable\": false,\n      \"rationale_a_rejected\": \"Pre-0.6.0 stress suite targeted the prior Python binding; semantics don't map onto current PyO3 surface without authoring a new harness.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B5\",\n      \"item\": \"typescript-observability-harness\",\n      \"missing\": \"@fathomdb/sdk-harness workspace in src/ts\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"src_ts_package_json\": \"Single package `fathomdb`, NOT a workspace. No `workspaces` key. No sdk-harness subpackage.\",\n        \"scripts_shape\": \"build:native runs napi build against ../rust/crates/fathomdb-napi; `test` script: `npm run build:debug && node --test dist/tests/*.test.js`\",\n        \"pre_0_6_0_invocation\": \"npm run build --workspace @fathomdb/sdk-harness + npm test --workspace @fathomdb/sdk-harness — workspace structure does not exist in 0.6.0\"\n      },\n      \"option_a_viable\": false,\n      \"rationale_a_rejected\": \"Pre-0.6.0 had a multi-workspace npm layout (fathomdb + sdk-harness); 0.6.0 collapsed to a single package. Re-introducing the workspace + porting the harness is a Phase 11+ topology decision, not workflow restoration.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": \"All five would-be jobs in benchmark-and-robustness.yml depend on substrate that does not exist in the 0.6.0 codebase: a benchmark harness + script, a scale test target, a tracing cargo feature + stress test, a Python stress test file, and a TS sdk-harness workspace. The pre-0.6.0 workflow was a thin shell over substrate that was deleted during the rewrite. Per `feedback_reliability_principles` (net-negative LoC, delete-before-add) and the prompt's explicit out-of-scope note (\\\"Any actual perf-evidence work (Pack 7 territory; this slice ships the workflow, not the experiments)\\\"), authoring the missing harnesses is out-of-scope for 12-B. The shippable artifact reduces to either (a) a workflow with zero non-noop jobs (worse than no workflow — wastes a weekly cron slot for a green-by-vacuity result) or (b) a workflow shell with all five jobs commented out with TODO references (writes a placeholder that misleads future readers).\",\n  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"STOP 12-B as currently scoped. Orchestrator decision required between three paths: (1) Close 12-B as no-op and demote ci-deferred.md § benchmark-and-robustness.yml to a Pack 7 prerequisite (recommended — most honest). (2) Re-scope 12-B narrowly to ship the workflow with only jobs whose substrate exists (currently: zero) plus follow-up tickets per dropped job. (3) Expand 12-B to include substrate authorship for one or more jobs — exits Wave 1 parallel budget, becomes its own multi-slice initiative. Do not respawn codex reviewer until orchestrator picks a path; there is no implementation diff to review.\",\n  \"discipline_notes\": [\n    \"Did not write a workflow yaml that would actionlint-green but reference non-existent test targets — actionlint validates syntax, not target existence, so a green actionlint on a workflow citing missing tests would be a false reassurance.\",\n    \"Did not stub bash scripts to satisfy `bash scripts/run-benchmarks.sh` — would violate prompt's 'Don't stub workflows that can't actually run' rule.\",\n    \"Did not invent cargo features or test files — would violate `feedback_reliability_principles` and exceed slice scope per the prompt's 'No data migration; no production code changes' bound.\"\n  ]\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":2,"oldLines":8,"newStart":2,"newLines":8,"lines":["   \"phase\": \"12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow\",","   \"baseline_sha\": \"f2f21b59338a706de625096b099b041e01c1a1c2\",","   \"branch\": \"phase-12-B-benchmark-robustness-workflow-20260517T195737Z\",","-  \"head_sha\": \"f2f21b59338a706de625096b099b041e01c1a1c2\",","-  \"commits\": [],","+  \"head_sha\": \"05b08af\",","+  \"commits\": [\"05b08af: docs(12-B): blocker report — benchmark-and-robustness substrate absent\"],","   \"workflow_file\": \".github/workflows/benchmark-and-robustness.yml\",","   \"workflow_line_count\": 0,","   \"jobs_restored\": [],"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
